inpluuium ‘ est locus sub eaelo in medio aedium relictus unde lumen deorsum caperet: ita dictus quod eo implueret’. Varro. Strictly it is a basin in the centre of the atrium into which the water fell from an opening in the roof (compluvium). The

arrangement in Greek houses was much the same: cistern in centre of the peristyle.
